	<td class="alt1" id="td_post_917071">
	
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_917071">Even with the new 1-75 expansion EQ1 is going to be hard pressed to appeal to new players. Face it, the game is more than 7 years old. How many new people are going to pick up a subscription-based game that old? The time when people used to bring their friends into EQ is over. The majority of people who are left in EQ either have no interest in playing anything else after EQ, or waiting for Vanguard.<br />
<br />
Will the new expansion bring in new blood? I'm sure. But I'm also sure that many of those new players won't last long. The expansion might make it easier and more fun to reach the level cap, but it won't bring new players up to par with those who have played &quot;the old way&quot;, in neither player skill nor character advancement.<br />
<br />
I don't think a long-term expansion of the player base is a viable goal for EQ anymore.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
