		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_918053">I was a player in EQ who LOVED starting a new character and progressiing through the old stuff that people identified as old yet I didn't pass through on my original journey through EQ on my main. <br />
<br />
Key to this experience for me was being able to confer a good bit of benefit upon the new alt\twink from my main character. This was in the form of gear without level limits or with spell buffs from higher level chars that, as you will recall, were not limited to what level player they could be casted upon at a certain point in EQ history. <br />
<br />
Those where the days. <br />
<br />
Then of course the nerfs came. Level limits on virtually everything led to the curtailing of twinking. Spell limits that established limits on what kind of beneficial spells from higher level players that could be casted on alts\twinks further discouraged twinking and trying out of a new class. <br />
<br />
Oddly enough, after some of these changes and coinciding with my guild's(Assent on MS server) killing with Quarm, I decided to really &quot;pack it in&quot; as far as EQ was concerned. <br />
<br />
If I could wave a wand and reverse some of the foregoing changes I mentioned, I could definitely see myself rolling an entirely new character and experiencing some of the new stuff that has come along since the nerfs. But I just dont see it happening because I dont see them rolling back those nerfs in  way that really welcomes twinking as a form of entertainment again like it was for many of us.</div>
