		<div id="post_message_918225">I have a solution.. Would be to costly for them though but it would probably work if they thought it was financially doable.<br />
<br />
My (undoable) idea:<br />
Next expansion is not a real expansion in the traditionall manner but really a new game with the latest technology and eye candy. Only a few of the old zones would be remade to start with since remaking them all with current tech would take ALOT of time.. Add some lore where Norrath gets destroyed by the gods or something (like eq2). Then they could market it as a new game which would attract alot of new players. The old players wouldn&#8217;t have to abandon their mains but they would still be inspired to roll up an alt to explore the 'new' old zones and the new quests and mobs there.<br />
Now this would piss of people who missed some of the old content but their are ways to get past this.<br />
<br />
To get to the new world (expansion) there would be 2 ways. <br />
A) Complete a mission that when you beat the final boss a Fairy comes and puts you to sleep and lets you sleep through the end of Norrath as we know it, thus saving your life. When you wake up your 5 years older and on the new server with all your gear and AAs intact. (Would take a day or two most likely, since it would mean a server transfer).<br />
B) Start a new char on the new server if you don&#8217;t bother about your main.<br />
<br />
Or they could put a time travel device in PoK that made it possible to travel back and forth between the new game and the old. This imo would be the best thing because no one could complain about missing some drop from oldworld after they transferred to new world, however this would probably not be doable. Technically I mean.<br />
<br />
WTF! I know nothing of this would be doable but a man can dream and fantasies while bored at work cant he?<br />
<br />
Ps. good post cloud.</div>
